results.name: Number of symmetrically inequivalent coincidence rotations of index n in lattice A_4.
comment: The overall number of coincidence rotations is 120 times higher. Some symmetrically distinct rotations generate the same coincidence site lattices, hence a(n) >= A331142(n). - _Andrey Zabolotskiy_, Jan 29 2020
link: Michael Baake and Peter Zeiner, Coincidences in 4 dimensions, Phil. Mag. 88 (2008), 2025-2032; arXiv:0712.0363 [math.MG]. See end of Section 3.
